Package edu.stanford.cs.pptx.code

This package defines a set of classes that make it possible to generate code traces in a PowerPoint slide.

See: Description

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    PPArray<T>
    This class represents an array in a code trace.
    PPCodeDisplaySlide
    This class defines a slide that can display a step-by-step trace of a program.
    PPCodeImage
    This class is a PPPicture subclass containing an image of a block of code rendered at high resolution.
    PPCodeTraceSlide
    This class defines a slide that can display a step-by-step trace of a program.
    PPConsole
    This class represents a console window in the pptx.code package.
    PPFunction
    This abstract class represents a function that the user can step through on a PPCodeTraceSlide.
    PPHeapStackViewer
    This class manages a heap-stack diagram.
    PPStackFrame
    This class represents a stack frame in the pptx.code package.
    PPValueTag
    This class represents a value that labels the value of an expression in a stack frame.
    PPVar<T>
    This class represents a typed variable in a stack frame.
    PPVariable
    This class represents a variable in a stack frame.
    PPWindowImage
    This class is a PPPicture subclass that represents an on-screen Macintosh window rendered at high resolution.
    PPWord
    This class represents a word in a memory viewer.
